laced on prompt-like dark photons are the most stringent to date for the mass\nrange $10.6 < m(A^{\\prime}) < 70$ GeV, and are comparable to the best existing\nlimits for $m(A^{\\prime}) < 0.5$ GeV. The search for long-lived dark photons is\nthe first to achieve sensitivity using a displaced-vertex signature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 8 Oct 2017 18:43:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 9 Feb 2018 18:09:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-14"}
